description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Minor Injury Unit at Kidderminster Hospital has an exciting opportunity for an Emergency Nurse Practitioner (ENP) to join our well established team of ENP’s and HCSW’s. The Minor Injury Unit is a completely nurse led unit who see, treat and discharge approximately 22,000 new patients per year. The successful candidate will be required to work autonomously and have an urgent care background .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a band 7 ENP the successful candidate is required to fulfil all the essential criteria on the personal specification including the following :&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ENP who works well under pressure, is able to work autonomously and manage their own case load.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The willingness to share new skills and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate how you keep up to date with current practice and legislation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to demonstrate a history of service improvement or ideas demonstrating your commitment to continually improving the patients journey in the every changing Health and Care Service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for delivering excellent patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of RCEM standards with in urgent care settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A willingness to learn new skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to communicate effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivers Patient focused care and enjoys been part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel you would like to be part of this well established Nurse Led Unit and are committed to ‘Putting the Patient First’ or would like further information please do not hesitate to contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For Informal enquiries please contact: Sally Bloomer (Ward Manager) on 01562 513039 or any ENPs in The Minor Injury Unit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
